{"ts":"2026-07-19T11:59:56.833Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"note_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T11:59:56.833Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/notes","value":[{"created_at":"2026-07-19T11:59:56.829Z","author":"maintainer-agent","text":"Implemented with full new-flag checklist: --add-ac/--remove-ac on pm update AND pm update-many. Core helpers splitAcceptanceCriteria/applyAcceptanceCriteriaMutations in core/item/parse.ts (criteria = \"; \"-separated segments; adds append in argv order + dedupe exact trimmed text; removals exact trimmed match; unmatched removals surface remove_ac_unmatched:<text> warnings — never a silent no-op). Additive mutation runs AFTER the scalar --ac replace so composition uses the replaced base. Guards: --unset ac × --add-ac/--remove-ac rejected; ownership-dependency-bypass scope rejects both; command_option_policy marks acceptanceCriteria for additive forms. update-many gets a composed preview plan (an --add-ac-only bulk run is actionable, not a skip; scalar+additive plans deduped into one acceptance_criteria change). Wiring: UPDATE_COMMANDER_OPTION_REGISTRATION_CONTRACTS (+snake aliases), registration-helpers, update-many hand-registered options + hidden aliases, UPDATE/UPDATE_MANY flag contracts, MCP tool-option-contracts (addAc/removeAc repeatable) + parameter tables + descriptions, zsh/fish completions for update+update-many, docs COMMANDS.md + AGENT_GUIDE.md, contracts snapshot regenerated after build. Manual verify: add/dedupe/remove/unmatched-warning all correct."}]}],"before_hash":"c131a98c37b46f10bdaa6dd81052ce27aa825b7c864f3ec443f1c6c034f090ba","after_hash":"1e51f256f686aee7e6c2e25b1aa44206e2d10ae1303262747315a933000881b8"}
